change the node version requirement for Travis (#46)

"stable" can switch major versions, which causes problems for projects that rely on (pre)compiled binaries: major version changes come with new versions of V8, which change the compilation targets and symbols, leading to broken compiles.

This switches the travis.yml requirement for Node over to the current LTS 6.*.*
